Task 3 – Coding & Collaboration Platforms Notes
Part A – Coding Practice (HackerRank)
Platform Used
HackerRank (hackerrank.com)

What I Did
Created an account on HackerRank and completed a beginner level challenge. A screenshot of the completed challenge has been added to this folder.

What I Learned
HackerRank helped me understand how online coding judges work. It evaluates your code automatically and gives instant feedback, which is very useful for practicing programming skills at my own pace.


Part B – Google Workspace Collaboration
What I Built
Created a Google Form titled 'Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz' containing 5 questions for my batchmates, including multiple choice and short answer questions. The responses are linked to a Google Sheet for easy tracking.

How These Tools Help Academically
These platforms will be extremely useful throughout my B.Tech journey. HackerRank will help me practice coding regularly and prepare for technical interviews and campus placements. Google Forms and Sheets are powerful collaboration tools that I can use for collecting data, conducting surveys, and working on group projects. Together, they build both my technical and organizational skills.


